Description: Fender Duo Sonic Second Version 1963 Production Very Good Condition with Hardshell Case OUR #MUS Duo Item Description From its exclusive local owner comes this very attractive and serviceable Fender Duo Sonic electric guitar. Manufacturer was Fender Musical Instruments Corp., of Fullerton, CA. From its 92200 range serial number, it was manufactured in 1963, part of the Second Version of the Duo Sonic series. Type is 3/4 sized, solid body electric 6 string guitar. Construction is American hardwood body, One piece plastic pick guard and humbucker pickup covers and string keys; maple neck with rosewood fingerboard; and steel bodied string studs and strap studs. Volume control knobs are alloy. All 21 frets are nickel alloy, the top nut is polymer. Finish is original semi gloss body and neck, with chrome plated string keys and hardware. Surface detractions are moderate, pirincipally adge dulling to the body finish and rest wear midways on the back of the neck. Neck is straight; and the keys and electronics are correct and functional. Hardshell case is unmarked and form fitting, but with wide head room. We estimate it was manufactured in the 1970s. We rate this guitar and its case as Very Good Condition, close to Excellent, 85 percent vicinity by our estimate, but photos ought to suffice for our distinguished shoppers to judge finish grade for themselves. Overall length is 37 inches, weight without any strap is 6 pounds 2 ounces. This guitar belonged to a local African American blues man who played between Birmingham and Chicago.
